Okay, I've got a riddle for you then!<br>
<br>
A coupla weeks ago, I took a bunch of clay.  I slipped it up with some water and molded into the cutest little doll!  Then I put in a pretty stone so that my doll was holding it, and then stuck it in the kiln so it would be in the fire until it was as hardened as it could be.  It's been out of the fire a long time now, and I've carried it all over the place since then.<br>
<br>
So here's the riddle: What is my doll made of?<br>
